a mass high tech “woman to watch” in  richard schotte director mr schotte is a successful investor and fund manager he is the president of the maine capital strategies corporation to which he brings more than forty years’ experience in financial and capital markets he spent ten years with the investment division of massachusetts mutual life insurance where he was a venture capitalist and later managed the company’s marketable bond operations after massmutual mr schotte spent twenty years as a fixedincome portfolio manager in los angeles with capital group whose subsidiary capital research and management company manages mutual funds under the name the american funds group matthias wagner director mr wagner is founder of systems he is a serial entrepreneur with extensive experience in bringing early stage hardware technologies to market his roles focus on technologyproductmarket fit key customer and partner development teambuilding strategic angel and vc fundraising patent portfolio building system architecture and development he has a bs in engineering physics from harvard and an mba in finance from mit sloan school sissi liu director ms liu is a cleantech executive with  years of sector experience most recently she headed up north american business development at joule unlimited technologies the pioneer in direct cotofuel production platform powered by sunlight at joule she managed the partnership with audi and developed partnerships internationally as well as in the us prior to joule she led the management of the seed fund at the massachusetts renewable energy trust which catalyzed seedstage clean energy technology companies additionally she has a background in energy policy consulting and investment banking with a focus on high tech and telecom she has a ba in economics and math from wellesley college and an mpp in public policy from harvard university james banks director mr banks is an experienced executive in process engineering and manufacturing industries he 